  "text": "Activity recognition (AR) is typically viewed as a classification problem where many traditional machine learning techniques can be applied [CITATION_1] . In most existing supervised learning approaches in AR, the training data is collected, a classification model is generated offline from the collected data, and finally the obtained model is deployed to recognise the activity. A wide range of classification models has been used for activity recognition such as Decision Trees, Naive Bayes and Support Vector Machines. A typical activity recognition system builds the learning model with annotated data to recognise new data and predict human activity type based on the learning model.",
